values.text:
**Project Closure Process**

When PM complete implementation phase, and get client formal confirmation, they can proceed with Closure process.  In closure phase, PM has to complete, **DAC** or **MAC** and **TimeSheet** as a primary closure document.  Along with primary closure docs, if any changes in Devices, has to prepare **SICC** form and also has to pass through **EOS and DOS Checklist** process if any network devices got involved.

Once required closure document prepared, get it validate with **Baseline Team** before submitting for client sign off.

Keep in mind that before you are able to close a project you have to complete the MANDATORY files 
<https://ibm.ent.box.com/folder/117499601997|[Template Box]>

Do you have a PCR that will result in negative TCV
PCR Stands for **Project Change Request**
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
**Neg TCV PCR Creation Process**
•	BEFORE raising a PCR, the PM/PgM will work together to prepare an estimate of the $ TCV in cases where the TCV is suspected to be negative.
•	The PM will prepare a traceability matrix file that ties out what has changed from the PWO to the actual implemented solution, outlining changes in device types, quantities or term, as applicable.
•	The PM will submit to the PE the estimated financial impact of the proposed PCR for PE review and written approval to raise the PCR.
•	Once received, this written approval must be submitted internally to the PD team along with the approved PCR Impact Assessment form for PCR creation.

**Process for PCRs in PE Approval Step**
•	RFS PD Team will submit a PCR to PE approval via email, and will notify the parties via dedicated channel, as appropriate (PE Approval channel is created in Slack)
•	The new SLO for PE approval will be  3 business days to allow for assessment of financial impact to accruals and revenue forecast. Previously, this was within 24 hours.
•	If the record is active in PE approval step for longer than 3 business days, an initial notification will be sent via email and Slack to the parties.
•	If the record remains in PE approval step for 5 business days, a final notification will be sent notifying the parties the record will be withdrawn by EOD. Sent via email and Slack to the parties.

**UKI IMPLEMENTATION DESIGNER**
This team is on charge of Firewall rules design & Server Build design for WPP

<https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=V3D2_MlQ1EqY8__KZK3Z6c-ktkuDhv5Pjlw-O7U7PJdUNTBET0hFWlpNTjlSTEpXUDlQN1k2Q0hURy4u|[REQUEST TOOL]>

1. Click on the Request Tool button to submit your access request.

2. You will be navigated to Access Request page. Fill up the form accordingly with your respective Name, Email & Account and submit the request.

3. The request will be process within 1-2 working days.

4. You will receive an email from Bluesight – that you have been invited to the Squad.5. Click on the profile link in the email.

6. Choose Global as the region and login using your intranet ID.7. Accept the invitation to the board.

RFS Stands for **Request For Service**

A **Request for service** is defined as revenue generation addendum business on existing strategic outsourcing accounts.

It starts with a request for either a new service or, in contracted services, any chance or enhancement requiring IBM to provide a proposed solution and price.

The end-to-end RFS processes manages the requests from initiation through requirements, proposal, pricing, client acceptance, implementation and billing.

*Americas Transformation & Refresh*

The Americas transformation and refresh team are tasked with analysis, planning, coordination and execution of infrastructure refresh and transformation in accordance to contract requirements.

**Guide to Raise an Implementation Designer Request**

1.	Click on the link CIC UK ID Request Tool in order to access tool. 
2.	Choose Global as the region.
3.	Login with your w3 intranet ID.
4.	Click  icon   (Card From the Template) on the right panel.   NOTE: DO NOT USE New Card or New Quick Card.      
5.	A new template form will be pop-up, remember to fill information below which required:                                                                                                                       
6.	Card Title – Brief title about your request
	•  Work State – Set as OPEN 
	• Description – Detail about your request
	• Account Name – Account for this request
	• Claim Code – Valid claim code for resource to claim to.
 	• TCV – Total Cost Value of this RFS (Put 0 if BAU)
	• Assignee – Leave the default value as it is – DO NOT CHANGE
7.	 Once filled up, Submit your request by click "Save & Close" button.  
8.	Your request will be in the queue stage – at this point – if you have any attachment, please do open the card and click on the "Attachment" button on the right of the card to attach supporting document i.e PWO, SAR, RFS document, BOM,  etc. (if any).
9.	Save and close. Your request will be in the queue stage where it will be reviewed and will be assigned to the next available resource to work on the request accordingly.

<https://www.bluesight.io/squads/27959/board|[CIC UK ID Bluesight Board]>

**SERVER BUILD PROCESS**
GSB is in charge of building servers and they work using the ADE tool

*Are you looking to build a Server?*
In the following attachment, you can find the procedure to raise a request in the tool.
If you need more information please use the Box Buttom, where you will find more information.

<https://ibm.ent.box.com/folder/118038240672|[ADE BOX FOLDER]>
•  <https://wpp-media.s3.us-south.cloud-object-storage.appdomain.cloud/ADE%20Requests%20User%20Guide.pdf|ADE Requests User Guide.pdf>
•  <https://wpp-media.s3.us-south.cloud-object-storage.appdomain.cloud/ADE%20BuildSheet%20Update%20Procedure.pdf|ADE BuildSheet Update Procedure.pdf>

**Claim Item Processing Requests **
________________________________________
All work item requests are submitted through the work item request form. 

<https://w3.ibm.com/tools/cio/forms/secure/org/app/a6b8fb23-acf8-4ffa-83f2-5354a0e4dd98/launch/index.html?form=F_Form1|[CREATE REQUEST]>

**General Information to be filled for any request type:**

Reference Number: this field is automatically populated with a system number. You can also edit it to add a reference that helps you identified the request.  

Requester: included your email.

Account name: select your Account Name.

Users to be copied: included any other emails that you need to be copied separated by coma.

Approval required: included the check if further approval is needed.

Approval email: when approval is needed included the check Approval Required. Select Yes or No depending on the case:  use Yes if you already had the approval and would attach to the form  or NO  if you need to request the approval using the form included the approver email on the Email field display. Please refer to your account's guidelines regarding approvals.
